](https://img.shields.io/badge/Google%20Cloud-4285F4?style=for-the-badge&logo=google-cloud&logoColor=white)\n\n---","metadata":{}},{"id":"8b531b72","cell_type":"markdown","source":"# 📋 Table of Contents\n\n1. **Workspace Overview** — Project structure & purpose\n2. **MCP Memory Graph** — Persistent knowledge architecture  \n3. **JudgeGuard Analysis** — MCP tool deep-dive (no execution)\n4. **Master Orchestration Protocol** — Governance framework\n5. **Work Logs & Audit Trail** — Decision history\n6. **Agent Coordination** — Multi-agent state machine\n7. **Kaggle Pipeline Results** — S6E3 Churn competition data\n8. **Architecture Visualization** — System diagrams","metadata":{}},{"id":"66ce7e28","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n# 1. 🏗️ Workspace Overview\n\n**Usisivac V6** is a Universal RAG Knowledge Ingestion & LLM Report System — a professional engine\nfor turning any codebase, documentation, or knowledge base into a searchable, AI-queryable vector store.\nOptimized for Kaggle competitions and agentic research.\n\n| Component | Purpose |\n|:---|:---|\n| `src/ingest.py` | Scans directories → chunks text → stores in ChromaDB |\n| `src/audit_ingest.py` | Ingests agent logs (WORK_LOG, GUARD_LOG) separately |\n| `src/generate_report.py` | RAG query → Groq/Llama-3.3 → structured Markdown report |\n| `src/dashboard.py` | Live CLI dashboard showing DB health and saturation |\n| `core/harvester_daemon.py` | Autonomous knowledge gathering from Kaggle & ArXiv |\n| `core/anti_simulation.py` | Physical write verification and hash-based integrity |\n| `core/trust_ledger.py` | Trust scoring and verification ledger |\n| `core/llm_client.py` | Multi-provider LLM client (Groq, OpenAI, Gemini) |\n| `core/neural_filter.py` | Neural content filtering and relevance scoring |\n| `core/rag_engine.py` | RAG retrieval engine with ChromaDB backend |\n\n### Tech Stack\n- **Vector DB**: ChromaDB\n- **Embeddings**: SentenceTransformers (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)\n- **LLM**: Groq (Llama-3.3-70b)\n- **Protocols**: Trinity Protocol (3-way relay), Anti-Simulation v3","metadata":{}},{"id":"f50f505a","cell_type":"code","source":"import json\nfrom datetime import datetime\nfrom IPython.display import display, HTML, Markdown\n\nprint(\"=\" * 70)\nprint(\"🏗️  USISIVAC V6 — Workspace Analysis Notebook\")\nprint(f\"📅  Generated: {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}\")\nprint(f\"👤  Author: Zoran | Kizabgd\")\nprint(f\"🏢  Antigravity Data Science\")\nprint(\"=\" * 70)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.490057Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.491318Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.516923Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.491278Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.515330Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"======================================================================\n🏗️  USISIVAC V6 — Workspace Analysis Notebook\n📅  Generated: 2026-04-28 18:24:05\n👤  Author: Zoran | Kizabgd\n🏢  Antigravity Data Science\n======================================================================\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":3},{"id":"34f90924","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n# 2. 🧠 MCP Memory Graph — Persistent Knowledge Architecture\n\nThe MCP (Model Context Protocol) Memory server maintains a **persistent knowledge graph**\nthat survives across sessions. It stores architectural decisions, pipeline configurations,\ndeployment configs, and development history as interconnected entities.\n\n### How It Works\n1. **Entities** are created with `mcp_memory_create_entities` — each has a name, type, and observations\n2. **Relations** link entities via `mcp_memory_create_relations` — e.g., \"governs\", \"applies_to\"\n3. **Retrieval** via `mcp_memory_read_graph` returns the full graph for context loading\n4. **Persistence** is stored at `~/.gemini/antigravity/knowledge_graph.json`\n\n> **Rule**: Every agent session begins with `read_graph` to load context before any action.","metadata":{}},{"id":"111423be","cell_type":"code","source":"# === MCP Memory Graph Structure (as read from mcp_memory_read_graph) ===\n\nmemory_entities = {\n    \"Agent_Hierarchy\": {\n        \"type\": \"ProjectRule\",\n        \"observations\": [\n            \"GEMINI CLI = Lead Architect / Project Manager. Has final say.\",\n            \"Qwen Code CLI = Core Developer. Implements logic.\",\n            \"Aider = Codebase Editor & Git Master. Multi-file refactoring.\",\n            \"Open Interpreter = System Executor / Tester.\",\n            \"Communication files: Work_log.md, Tabla.md, Working_fall.md.\",\n            \"Rule: Do NOT edit same files at the same time as another agent.\"\n        ]\n    },\n    \"S6E3_Churn_Pipeline\": {\n        \"type\": \"KaggleProject\",\n        \"observations\": [\n            \"Competition: Kaggle Playground Series S6E3 - Telco Customer Churn\",\n            \"Target: AUC 0.920+\",\n            \"Models: XGBoost, LightGBM, CatBoost (GPU optional)\",\n            \"Ensemble: Hill Climbing on OOF predictions\",\n            \"OptBinning WoE implemented for categorical features\",\n            \"Ridge Stacking meta-learner added\",\n            \"Best Public LB: 0.91548\"\n        ]\n    },\n    \"Pipeline_File_Map\": {\n        \"type\": \"CodeMap\",\n        \"observations\": [\n            \"feature_extractor.py — KNN features, target encoding (5-fold)\",\n            \"models.py — XGB/LGBM/CatBoost, residual boosting\",\n            \"ensemble.py — HillClimber: GPU accelerated via cupy\",\n            \"main.py — run_pipeline() orchestrator\",\n            \"utils.py — GPU detection, data paths, logging\"\n        ]\n    },\n    \"Portfolio_Infrastructure\": {\n        \"type\": \"DeploymentConfig\",\n        \"observations\": [\n            \"Cloudflare Worker: https://portfolio-ai.kiza101288.workers.dev\",\n            \"Cloudflare Pages: https://kiza-portfolio.pages.dev\",\n            \"D1 tables: agent_logs, rules (JudgeGuard TrustScores)\",\n            \"Live chat: polls /agent-logs every 3s\"\n        ]\n    },\n    \"Working_Fall_Rules\": {\n        \"type\": \"BestPractices\",\n        \"observations\": [\n            \"NEVER use `cat` to rewrite files. Use sed or replace tools.\",\n            \"ALWAYS use Kaggle API for data downloads and submissions.\",\n            \"Memory MCP is RAM-only by default — set MEMORY_FILE_PATH for persistence.\"\n        ]\n    },\n    \"MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT\": {\n        \"type\": \"MasterProtocol\",\n        \"observations\": [\n            \"AUTHORITY: Single source of truth for ALL Antigravity agents.\",\n            \"Flow: task_boundary → sequential-thinking → Skill Manager → JudgeGuard → Execute → JudgeGuard → notify_user\",\n            \"MAJOR ACTIONS require JudgeGuard pre/post check\",\n            \"CHECKPOINT: After each step: mark [x], git commit, update WORK_LOG\"\n        ]\n    },\n    \"Usisivac_V6_Core\": {\n        \"type\": \"ProjectComponent\",\n        \"observations\": [\n            \"Multi-agent system: Orchestrator, Coder, Guardian, Research, Critic\",\n            \"DeBERTa-v3 for sentiment; DistilRoBERTa-v2 for production\",\n            \"PEFT (LoRA) for domain adaptation\",\n            \"context.json = single machine-readable state snapshot\"\n        ]\n    },\n    \"Antigravity_Extensions\": {\n        \"type\": \"SystemComponent\",\n        \"observations\": [\n            \"gemini-superpowers: Skills, Commands, Hooks\",\n            \"ComputerUse: Playwright MCP server\",\n            \"GeminiCloudAssist: GCP investigations\",\n            \"gcloud: Compute, SQL, GKE, Run agent\",\n            \"judge-guard MCP: registered from mcp_judge_guard.py\"\n        ]\n    }\n}\n\nmemory_relations = [\n    (\"Agent_Hierarchy\", \"governs\", \"S6E3_Churn_Pipeline\"),\n    (\"Working_Fall_Rules\", \"applies_to\", \"S6E3_Churn_Pipeline\"),\n    (\"Working_Fall_Rules\", \"applies_to\", \"Portfolio_Infrastructure\"),\n    (\"S6E3_Churn_Pipeline\", \"uses_modules_from\", \"Pipeline_File_Map\"),\n    (\"MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT\", \"overrides\", \"Agent_Hierarchy\"),\n    (\"MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT\", \"applies_to\", \"S6E3_Churn_Pipeline\"),\n    (\"MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT\", \"applies_to\", \"Portfolio_Infrastructure\"),\n    (\"MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT\", \"utilizes\", \"Antigravity_Extensions\"),\n    (\"Portfolio_Infrastructure\", \"serves\", \"Agent_Hierarchy\"),\n]\n\nprint(f\"📊 MCP Memory Graph Statistics:\")\nprint(f\"   Entities: {len(memory_entities)}\")\nprint(f\"   Relations: {len(memory_relations)}\")\nprint(f\"   Entity Types: {sorted(set(v['type'] for v in memory_entities.values()))}\")\nprint()\n\nfor name, data in memory_entities.items():\n    print(f\"🔹 {name} [{data['type']}]\")\n    for obs in data['observations'][:3]:\n        print(f\"   → {obs}\")\n    if len(data['observations']) > 3:\n        print(f\"   → ... +{len(data['observations'])-3} more observations\")\n    print()\n\nprint(\"\\n🔗 Entity Relations:\")\nfor src, rel, dst in memory_relations:\n    print(f\"   {src} ──[{rel}]──▶ {dst}\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.518904Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.519747Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.548872Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.519699Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-28T18:24:05.546845Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"📊 MCP Memory Graph Statistics:\n   Entities: 8\n   Relations: 9\n   Entity Types: ['BestPractices', 'CodeMap', 'DeploymentConfig', 'KaggleProject', 'MasterProtocol', 'ProjectComponent', 'ProjectRule', 'SystemComponent']\n\n🔹 Agent_Hierarchy [ProjectRule]\n   → GEMINI CLI = Lead Architect / Project Manager. Has final say.\n   → Qwen Code CLI = Core Developer. Implements logic.\n   → Aider = Codebase Editor & Git Master. Multi-file refactoring.\n   → ... +3 more observations\n\n🔹 S6E3_Churn_Pipeline [KaggleProject]\n   → Competition: Kaggle Playground Series S6E3 - Telco Customer Churn\n   → Target: AUC 0.920+\n   → Models: XGBoost, LightGBM, CatBoost (GPU optional)\n   → ... +4 more observations\n\n🔹 Pipeline_File_Map [CodeMap]\n   → feature_extractor.py — KNN features, target encoding (5-fold)\n   → models.py — XGB/LGBM/CatBoost, residual boosting\n   → ensemble.py — HillClimber: GPU accelerated via cupy\n   → ... +2 more observations\n\n🔹 Portfolio_Infrastructure [DeploymentConfig]\n   → Cloudflare Worker: https://portfolio-ai.kiza101288.workers.dev\n   → Cloudflare Pages: https://kiza-portfolio.pages.dev\n   → D1 tables: agent_logs, rules (JudgeGuard TrustScores)\n   → ... +1 more observations\n\n🔹 Working_Fall_Rules [BestPractices]\n   → NEVER use `cat` to rewrite files. Use sed or replace tools.\n   → ALWAYS use Kaggle API for data downloads and submissions.\n   → Memory MCP is RAM-only by default — set MEMORY_FILE_PATH for persistence.\n\n🔹 MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT [MasterProtocol]\n   → AUTHORITY: Single source of truth for ALL Antigravity agents.\n   → Flow: task_boundary → sequential-thinking → Skill Manager → JudgeGuard → Execute → JudgeGuard → notify_user\n   → MAJOR ACTIONS require JudgeGuard pre/post check\n   → ... +1 more observations\n\n🔹 Usisivac_V6_Core [ProjectComponent]\n   → Multi-agent system: Orchestrator, Coder, Guardian, Research, Critic\n   → DeBERTa-v3 for sentiment; DistilRoBERTa-v2 for production\n   → PEFT (LoRA) for domain adaptation\n   → ... +1 more observations\n\n🔹 Antigravity_Extensions [SystemComponent]\n   → gemini-superpowers: Skills, Commands, Hooks\n   → ComputerUse: Playwright MCP server\n   → GeminiCloudAssist: GCP investigations\n   → ... +2 more observations\n\n\n🔗 Entity Relations:\n   Agent_Hierarchy ──[governs]──▶ S6E3_Churn_Pipeline\n   Working_Fall_Rules ──[applies_to]──▶ S6E3_Churn_Pipeline\n   Working_Fall_Rules ──[applies_to]──▶ Portfolio_Infrastructure\n   S6E3_Churn_Pipeline ──[uses_modules_from]──▶ Pipeline_File_Map\n   MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT ──[overrides]──▶ Agent_Hierarchy\n   MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT ──[applies_to]──▶ S6E3_Churn_Pipeline\n   MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT ──[applies_to]──▶ Portfolio_Infrastructure\n   MASTER_ORCHESTRATION_PERSISTENT ──[utilizes]──▶ Antigravity_Extensions\n   Portfolio_Infrastructure ──[serves]──▶ Agent_Hierarchy\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":4},{"id":"ce3ccef3","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n# 3. 🛡️ JudgeGuard — MCP Tool Deep-Dive (Analysis Only)\n\n> ⚠️ **Note**: This section ANALYZES the JudgeGuard system without executing it.\n> Per user request, we inspect the code architecture and explain its application.\n\n## 3.1 MCP Wrapper: `mcp_judge_guard.py`\n\nThe MCP wrapper is a lightweight **FastMCP** server (37 lines) that exposes a single tool:\n`run_judge_guard(action: str) → str`\n\n```python\nfrom mcp.server.fastmcp import FastMCP\nimport subprocess, os\n\nmcp = FastMCP(\"JudgeGuardServer\")\n\n@mcp.tool()\ndef run_judge_guard(action: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Runs judge_guard.py for action verification.\"\"\"\n    script_path = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), \"judge_guard.py\")\n    result = subprocess.run(\n        [\"python3\", script_path, \"--action\", action],\n        capture_output=True, text=True, check=False\n    )\n    if result.returncode == 0:\n        return f\"✅ ALLOWED (Exit 0):\\n{result.stdout}\"\n    else:\n        return f\"🛑 BLOCKED (Exit {result.returncode}):\\n{result.stderr}\"\n```\n\n### Key Design Decisions:\n1. **Subprocess isolation** — judge_guard.py runs in its own process\n2. **Exit code protocol** — `EXIT 0 = PROCEED`, `EXIT 1 = HALT`\n3. **Transparent output** — stdout/stderr captured and returned to agent","metadata":{}},{"id":"884894f8","cell_type":"code","source":"# === JudgeGuard Architecture Analysis (NO EXECUTION) ===\n\njudgeguard_analysis = {\n    \"version\": \"v2.1 (FINAL PRODUCTION AUDIT)\",\n    \"total_lines\": 799,\n    \"file\": \"judge_guard.py\",\n    \"mcp_wrapper\": \"mcp_judge_guard.py (37 lines)\",\n    \"components\": {\n        \"BlockJudge\": {\n            \"type\": \"Pure Python Rule Engine (Fallback)\",\n            \"lines\": \"162-208\",\n            \"purpose\": \"Rule-based evaluator when LLM is unavailable\",\n            \"forbidden_patterns\": [\n                \"rm -rf\", \"DROP TABLE\", \"DELETE FROM\", \"FORMAT C:\",\n                \"sudo rm\", \"os.system\", \"exec(\", \"eval(\",\n                \"subprocess.call\", \"__import__\", \"shutil.rmtree\"\n            ],\n            \"safety_keywords\": [\"backup\", \"verify\", \"confirm\", \"validate\", \"check\"],\n            \"risk_levels\": [\"HIGH (violations found)\", \"MEDIUM (no safety keywords)\", \"LOW (safe)\"]\n        },\n        \"JudgeGuardLite\": {\n            \"type\": \"Offline Runtime Safety\",\n            \"lines\": \"228-301\",\n            \"purpose\": \"Memory monitoring, CSV validation, OOM prevention\",\n            \"features\": [\n                \"check_memory(threshold_mb=13000) — monitors RAM usage\",\n                \"validate_csv(df, required_cols) — checks NaN, duplicates, columns\",\n                \"safe_save(df, filename) — validates then saves with fallback\"\n            ]\n        },\n        \"APIJudge\": {\n            \"type\": \"Tier 1 API Judge\",\n            \"lines\": \"50-74 / 317-341\",\n            \"purpose\": \"OpenAI-compatible API judge (Ollama/Docker)\",\n            \"model\": \"qwen2.5:3b\",\n            \"endpoint\": \"/v1/chat/completions\"\n        },\n        \"DualLLMJudge\": {\n            \"type\": \"Multi-tier Inference Manager\",\n            \"lines\": \"76-112 / 343-398\",\n            \"purpose\": \"Manages Senior (Qwen2.5-1.5B) and Junior (DistilGPT2) judges\",\n            \"features\": [\n                \"judge_content() — Tier 1 API → Local Senior fallback\",\n                \"debate() — Senior vs Junior adver